<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <meta http-equiv="x-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
        <title>Guru</title>
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
                background-color: #ffebee;
                text-align: center;
            }
            #cover, #message, #nextPage {
                padding: 30px;
                border-radius: 15px;
                box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
                max-width: 600px;
                margin: auto;
            }
            #cover {
                background-color: #fce4ec;
            }
            #message {
                background-color: #fff0f5;
                display: none;
                animation: fadeIn 1.5s forwards;
            }
            #nextPage {
                background-color: #ffffff;
                display: none;
                animation: fadeIn 1.5s forwards;
            }
            .letter-title {
                color: #b30000;
                font-size: 28px;
                font-weight: bold;
                text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            }
            .letter-text {
                color: #333;
                font-size: 18px;
                line-height: 1.6;
                font-style: italic;
                text-align: justify;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            button {
                background-color: #b30000;
                color: white;
                padding: 10px 20px;
                border: none;
                border-radius: 5px;
                font-size: 16px;
                cursor: pointer;
                transition: 0.3s;
            }
            button:hover {
                background-color: #800000;
            }
            img {
                width: 300px;
                height: auto;
                border-radius: 10px;
                margin: 20px 0;
            }
            @keyframes fadeIn {
                to {
                    opacity: 1;
                    transform: translateY(0);
                }
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="cover">
            <h1> Happy Valentine's Day!</h1>
			<img src="https://i.postimg.cc/0bjHDSxJ/40.jpg" alt="card">
            
            <br>
            <button onclick="opencard()"> Click To Open! </button>
        </div>

        <div id="message">
            <h1 class="letter-title">A Letter to My Soul!</h1>
            <p class="letter-text">
                Guru Moorthy, <br><br>
                There aren’t enough words in the world to express how deeply I feel for you, but I’ll try. In every moment, you show me a love that goes beyond the traditional. You’ve never just been my husband—you’ve been my best friend, my biggest supporter, and the one person who has cared for me like I’m the most important thing in the world. You’ve treated me like a princess, with kindness, patience, and so much tenderness. <br><br>
                You’ve always been there for me in ways I never expected, offering a constant presence of love and understanding. When I needed someone to lean on, you were there, never asking for anything in return, only wanting to see me happy. I’m not sure how I got so lucky, but I thank the stars every day for you. <br><br>
                You’re not just my partner; you’re my heart’s safest place. You’ve never treated me like “just a wife”—you’ve been my everything. You make me feel cherished in ways I can hardly put into words. And even though life’s journey might not always fit the typical mold, you’ve shown me that love doesn’t need to be conventional—it just needs to be real. <br><br>
                Thank you for being the incredible person you are. I’m so proud to have you by my side, and I’ll forever cherish the bond we share. You are not only my husband but my best friend, my protector, and the love of my life. <br><br>
                With all my love, <br>
                Your Deepi. 
            </p>
            <button onclick="nextPage()"> Click To Next Page! </button>
        </div>

        <div id="nextPage">
            <h1 class="letter-title">For You, My Love</h1>
			<img src="https://i.postimg.cc/YjbsvRcH/00.jpg" alt="cover">
			
           
            <br>
            <button onclick="closecard()"> Click To Close! </button>
        </div>

        <script>
            function opencard() {
                document.getElementById('cover').style.display = 'none';
                document.getElementById('message').style.display = 'block';
            }
            function nextPage() {
                document.getElementById('message').style.display = 'none';
                document.getElementById('nextPage').style.display = 'block';
            }
            function closecard() {
                document.getElementById('nextPage').style.display = 'none';
                document.getElementById('cover').style.display = 'block';
            }
        </script>
    </body>
</html>
